extends layout.pug

block content
    .row
        .col-12
            h1.content-title
                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-hand-pointer-o
                | Buttons
    .row
        .col-md-12
            .box
                .box-body
                    h2 Colors
                    p To create a nice button, just choose a class: #[code btn-primary], #[code btn-success], #[code btn-info], #[code btn-primary], #[code btn-warning], #[code btn-danger].
                    br
                    .text-center
                        button.btn-default .btn-default
                        button.btn-success .btn-success
                        button.btn-info .btn-info
                        button.btn-primary .btn-primary
                        button.btn-warning .btn-warning
                        button.btn-danger .btn-danger
                    hr
                    h2 Disabled
                    p You have two options to disable a button:
                    ul
                        li Use the #[b attribute] #[code disabled] and really disable it;
                        li Use the #[b class] #[code disabled] and only make it look disabled.
                    p When you use only the class, actions continue to be triggered when you click the button.
                    p In the example bellow, all buttons would trigger an alert, but the first three are disabled with the attribute, so it won't work. Try clicking on them:
                    br
                    .text-center
                        button(onclick='alert("I am disabled")' disabled).btn-default Attribute
                        button(onclick='alert("I am disabled")' disabled).btn-success Attribute
                        button(onclick='alert("I am disabled")' disabled).btn-info Attribute
                        button(onclick='alert("I am disabled")').btn-primary.disabled Class
                        button(onclick='alert("I am disabled")').btn-warning.disabled Class
                        button(onclick='alert("I am disabled")').btn-danger.disabled Class
                    br
                    p Note that links don't support the #[code disabled] attribute, so they will behave as if using the class instead of the attribute.
                    p To get a behavior close to the disabled button, you can use the class #[code disable-pointer] so the element wont respond to mouse events (click and hover), and use the a negative #[code tabindex] to prevent the focus on keyboard navigation.
                    hr
                    h2 Sizes
                    p To set a different size, just add the class #[code btn-xs], #[code btn-sm] or #[code btn-lg] to your button.
                    br
                    br
                    .text-center
                        button.btn-default.btn-xs .btn-xs
                        button.btn-default.btn-sm .btn-sm
                        button.btn-default Default
                        button.btn-default.btn-lg .btn-lg
                    hr
                    h2 Color Trigger
                    p LiteAdmin also provides discrete buttons, that are highlighted when the user needs them.
                    p Using it is easy: add the class #[code color-trigger] to any element and the buttons inside it will be discrete, being highlighted when the user hovers the given element.
                    p In the example below, the class was added in the table's rows:
                    br
                    .row.justify-content-center
                        .table.col-sm-10.col-lg-8
                            table
                                thead
                                    tr
                                        th User
                                        th Email
                                        th.text-center Actions
                                tbody
                                    tr.btn-color-trigger
                                        td John Doe
                                        td john.doe@email.com
                                        td.text-right
                                            button.btn-sm.btn-primary
                                                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-search
                                                | Profile
                                            button.btn-sm.btn-warning
                                                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-edit
                                                | Edit
                                            button.btn-sm.btn-danger
                                                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-trash
                                                | Delete
                                    tr.btn-color-trigger
                                        td John Doe
                                        td john.doe#[wbr]@email.com
                                        td.text-right
                                            button.btn-sm.btn-primary
                                                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-search
                                                | Profile
                                            button.btn-sm.btn-warning
                                                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-edit
                                                | Edit
                                            button.btn-sm.btn-danger
                                                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-trash
                                                | Delete
                                    tr.btn-color-trigger
                                        td John Doe
                                        td john.doe#[wbr]@email.com
                                        td.text-right
                                            button.btn-sm.btn-primary
                                                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-search
                                                | Profile
                                            button.btn-sm.btn-warning
                                                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-edit
                                                | Edit
                                            button.btn-sm.btn-danger
                                                i.fa.fa-fw.fa-trash
                                                | Delete
                    p In devices that are not good to hover (like touchscreens) or in browsers that we can't detect it, the buttons are colored by default, for accessibility.
                    hr
                    h2 Pagination
                    p If you need pagination, we've got you covered. Just create a #[code #{'<div class="pagination">'}] with links inside, and you're good to go.
                    br
                    .pagination.text-center
